                     <interp inst="t18480918-2232-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp>, stealing 1 handkerchief, value 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 6<hi rend="italic">d</hi>.; the goods of <persName id="t18480918-name-1012" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18480918-name-1012" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480918-name-1012" type="surname" value="BARTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480918-name-1012" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18480918-2232-offence-1 t18480918-name-1012"></join>John Barton</persName>, from his person.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480918-name-1013" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480918-name-1013" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480918-name-1013" type="surname" value="BARTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480918-name-1013" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN BARTON</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Westminster-road, and am an auctioneer. On 8th Sept. I was in Oakley-street, Westminster-road—I felt an attack on my pocket—I turned and saw a person turn up a street, who I have no doubt was the prisoner, by his brown coat which he wore—I went into the main street—there was a crowd with some music—I stopped for a moment, and found a second attack on my pocket—I turned and saw the prisoner dose to me—he went away, and I pursued him—he was stopped, and I went up—I put my band into his pocket, and found a handkerchief—he said, "That is not your handkerchief," and I think he said, "That is cotton"—mine was a silk handkerchief.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480918-name-1014" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480918-name-1014" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480918-name-1014" type="surname" value="COCKERELL"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480918-name-1014" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM COCKERELL</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman, L</hi> 108). I heard a cry of "Stop thief!"—I saw the prisoner stopped opposite Allen-street—I went up, and Mr. Barton accused him of stealing his handkerchief—the prisoner said, "I have not got it; yours was a silk one"—he took a cotton handkerchief out of his pocket, and said, "That is not yours; that is a cotton one."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480918-name-1015" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480918-name-1015" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480918-name-1015" type="surname" value="BARTON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480918-name-1015" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN BARTON</persName>
                  </hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">re-examined.</hi> I saw nobody with the prisoner—there might have been, as there was a crowd of people—he was close behind me, and nobody else near me.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> He said, "That lad stole my silk handkerchief;" that was why I said mine was cotton. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> I did not say anything about a silk hand<lb></lb>kerchief.</p>
